\gamma(x,a)
e^x \gamma(x,a) = \sum_{k=0}^{\infty} \frac{x^{k+a}}{a (a+1)\ldots(a+k)} 
R(n) = \frac{n! e^n}{n^n} \frac{\gamma(n,n)}{(n-1)!} \implies S(n) = \frac{\gamma(n,n)}{\Gamma(n)}
